By ADEJUWON OSUNNUYI The Chairman of Surulere Local Government Area, Lagos, Hon. Tajudeen Ajide, has congratulated the Speaker of the House of Representatives, Rt. Hon. Femi Gbajabiamila on his election. The Chairman, in a statement released on Thursday, said “Rt. Hon. Femi Gbajabiamila, as Speaker of the House of Representatives, is a competent and commendable choice given his robust legislative experience and constructive contributions at plenaries and on national discourses”. “I felicitate with our toiling party members and voters in Surulere Federal Constituency I on this shared glory.” Ajide also hailed Senator Oluremi Tinubu, saying her return as the representative of Lagos Central Senatorial district was reward for quality representation of her constituents. He said: “No doubt, Nigerians eagerly await more democracy dividends from the federal government based on their hope of a greater accord between the Executive and the newly inaugurated 9th National Assembly. “Apparently, President Muhammadu Buhari’s “Next Level” agenda is achievable with the present arrangement. I equally congratulate the President and our leader, Asiwaju Bola Tinubu for their efforts at this critical juncture of Nigeria’s democracy.” 